{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6580b611-3985-40cf-a20d-70d522db1db9","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr if you prefer filtering by class name explicitly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. If you have multiple test projects, you can also specify the project path:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test path/to/YourTests.csproj --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e316ef32-d4ae-4c25-8ce3-83268da524aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to run only a specific test class (`ReportExporterTests`) using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about dotnet CLI usage.","outputTokens":204,"requestId":"E3DE:52A37:5AC8B1:68D574:6A05254A"},"id":"603ec42e-480d-4ceb-bcef-8dc86f335bb5","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:28:49.178Z","parentId":"20d6d7a4-4d05-460f-9b94-1c9382387929"}
